Function Reference/comments rss link « WordPress Codex
-----------

This function has been deprecated, please use
[post\_comments\_feed\_link()](/Function_Reference/post_comments_feed_link "Function Reference/post comments feed link").

Much like an RSS feed for your WordPress blog, this feature will display
a link to the [RSS](/Glossary#RSS "Glossary") feed for a given post's
comments. By implementing the feature, your readers will be able to
track the comment thread for a given post, perhaps encouraging them to
stay connected to the conversation.

This tag must be within [The Loop](/The_Loop "The Loop"), or the loop
set up for comments.

Usage
-----

`  <?php comments_rss_link('text', 'file'); ?> `

Example
-------

Displays the link to the comment's RSS feed, using "comment feed" as the
link text.

    <?php comments_rss_link('comment feed'); ?>

Parameters
----------

 'text' 
:   (*string*) Link text for the comments RSS link. Defaults to
    `'Comments RSS'`.
 'file' 
:   (*string*) The file the link points to. Defaults to
    `'wp-commentsrss2.php'`.

Changelog
---------

-   Deprecated: [2.5.0](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5") use
    [post\_comments\_feed\_link()](/Function_Reference/post_comments_feed_link "Function Reference/post comments feed link")
-   Since: 1.0.1

